1. The firſt was by a Spaniſh Armado, ſtiled the invincible Armado, when they came to rebuild their Romiſh Jericho, furniſhed with all Inſtruments of Cruelty, and hearts full of confidence that the work would be done, that they ſhould cut us off from being a Nation, and that the name of Proteſtant, of Heretick ſhould be had no more in remembrance. They were ſo big with hopes, as to ſay with Moab, (before the fight) 
                     Ʋp Moab to the ſpoil; 
                  2 King, 3. 21, 22, 23. up Rome, to the ſpoil, for the Victory ſhall be ours; but God, in mercy to us, Croſſed, Curſed that deſign and wonderfully diſappointed that hopeful enterprize.
